---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/global.css";
---

<Layout title="TRIUMF Co-op">
  <section class="p-8 sm:p-12 md:p-16 lg:p-24 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <a href="/#experience" class="text-sm text-gray-500 hover:underline">
      ← Back to Home
    </a>

    <h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900">
      TRIUMF Particle Accelerator
    </h1>

    <p class="mt-2 text-lg text-gray-600">
      Student Research Assistant - PIONEER Experiment | Jan 2025 - May 2025
    </p>

    <div class="mt-6 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
      <p>
        During my time at TRIUMF, I worked with the PIONEER group on a rare pion decay
        experiment. The PIONEER experiment will be conducted in a large liquid xenon
        (LXe) calorimeter, and continuous monitoring of the LXe's purity is required
        during the experiment.
      </p>
      <p>
        To achieve this, I was involved in the testing and development of a Purity
        Monitor Assembly (PUMA) and its calibration device to be used in high-precision
        experiments with LXe calorimeters.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
      <p>
        I conducted physics simulations of PUMA to better understand particle behaviour
        inside the assembly in various media. I used COMSOL Multiphysics to perform
        electrostatic finite element analysis on the CAD model of PUMA.
      </p>
      <p>
        I also wrote C++ scripts in Linux using Garfield++, a library written by CERN
        for detailed simulation of particle drift in detectors. Some results are shown
        below.
      </p>
    </div>

    <br />

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <figure>
        <img src="/sim1.png" class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded-md shadow-lg" />
        <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
          PUMA E-Field model
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure>
        <img src="/sim2.png" class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded-md shadow-lg" />
        <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
          Vacuum setup
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure>
        <img src="/sim3.jpg" class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded-md shadow-lg" />
        <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
          Garfield++ Python simulation setup
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
      <p>
        Further, I designed and built a vacuum system to perform initial tests of the
        calibration device for PUMA.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mt-6">
      <figure>
        <img src="/vac1.jpg" class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded-md shadow-lg" />
        <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
          Vacuum assembly
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure>
        <img src="/vac2.jpg" class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded-md shadow-lg" />
        <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
           PUMA calibration device integration
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure>
        <img src="/vac3.jpg" class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded-md shadow-lg" />
        <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
          Vacuum setup
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
      <p>
        After ensuring the vacuum system could reliably reach low pressures over
        extended periods of time, I began testing PUMA's calibration device inside the
        vacuum system.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mt-6">
      <figure>
        <img src="/test1.jpg" class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded-md shadow-lg" />
        <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
          Instrumentation
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure>
        <img src="/test2.png" class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded-md shadow-lg" />
        <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
          Data analysis
        </figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure>
        <img src="/test3.jpg" class="w-full aspect-square object-cover rounded-md shadow-lg" />
        <figcaption class="mt-1 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
          Experimental setup
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>

    <!-- ✅ Single-image block example -->
    <figure class="mt-8">
      <img
        src="/vac3.jpg"
        class="w-full aspect-[4/3] rounded-md shadow-lg"
        alt="Single simulation result"
      />
      <figcaption class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
        Vacuum Setup.
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <div class="mt-6 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed space-y-4">
      <p>
        Working at TRIUMF was a great experience and I enjoyed being in charge of a
        project within a larger cutting-edge physics context.
      </p>
      <p>
        At the end of my term, I participated in TRIUMF's co-op poster session and was
        awarded 2nd place.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">
        Poster for TRIUMF undergrad poster session
      </h2>
      <iframe src="/final_poster.pdf" class="w-full h-[600px] border rounded-lg"></iframe>
      <a href="/final_poster.pdf" download class="text-sm text-blue-600 underline">
        Click here to download
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Co-op Term Final Report</h2>
      <iframe src="/final_report.pdf" class="w-full h-[600px] border rounded-lg"></iframe>
      <a href="/final_report.pdf" download class="text-sm text-blue-600 underline">
        Click here to download
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
